
SOFTWARE EVALUATION LICENSE AGREEMENT

This software license agreement applies to the RT-SBS software, hereinafter referred to as the “Software”, available for download from this website and constitutes a legal agreement between the person or entity downloading the Software, hereinafter referred to as “Licensee”, and University of Liège, hereinafter referred to as “ULiège". By downloading, installing and otherwise using the Software, Licensee is automatically agreeing to and show that he has read and understood the terms and conditions contained in this Software Evaluation License.


1. 	BACKGROUND 

ULiège owns certain software for use for background detection and subtraction in video sequences that  implements a method covered by patents also owned by ULiège. The software and the patents (hereinafter “the Technology”) were developed by the laboratory of Professor Marc Van Droogenbroeck, the research unit for signal and image exploitation of the Electrical Engineering and Computer Science of the University of Liège. This software is entitled « RT-SBS ». 

Licensee desires to acquire a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable, limited license to use such software for the purposes of evaluating Technology.

Licensee shall use such software for the sole purpose of determining its interest in acquiring a commercial license on the Technology and solely upon the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement. 



2.	 DEFINITIONS
 
2.1 “Prototype” means any software to be developed by Licensee that includes or incorporates the Software, in whole or in parts, or elements based on or deriving from the Software. 

2.2 “Software” means the source code and binary files known as « RT-SBS » provided to Licensee pursuant to this Agreement.  Software includes the “RT-SBS ” Reference implementation in python and any other material relating to the Software that may be provided by ULiège to Licensee in connection with this Agreement.


